{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:30:39.966038+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\"issues\":[{\"number\":1,\"title\":\"from_file silently returns empty AudioSegment when path doesn\\u0026#39;t exist\",\"body\":\"Running into something weird on my CI. When a wav file path is wrong\\n(typo, file not yet copied into the build, etc.), `AudioSegment.from_file`\\nreturns what looks like an empty AudioSegment instead of raising. The\\nfailure shows up much later when I try to slice or export.\\n\\nMinimal reproducer:\\n\\n    from pydub import AudioSegment\\n\\n    # this file does NOT exist on disk\\n    seg = AudioSegment.from_file(\\u0026#34;/tmp/does-not-exist.wav\\u0026#34;)\\n    print(len(seg))  # I expected an exception, got: 0\\n    print(seg.dBFS)  # then: -inf\\n\\nMy read of pydub/utils.py mediainfo_json and audio_segment.py\\nfrom_file is that ffmpeg gets invoked with a missing input and\\nsilently returns nothing useful; the from_file path then proceeds\\nas if it had a valid 0-length segment.\\n\\nIs this intended (treat missing files as 0-length)? Or should\\nfrom_file raise `CouldntDecodeError` (or `FileNotFoundError`) when\\nthe input doesn\\u0026#39;t exist? Happy to send a PR for either direction.\\n\\nffmpeg version: 6.0\\npydub version: 0.25.1\\n\\n---\\n\\nUpdate: I ran `ffmpeg -version` on the CI worker that was producing\\nthis and got `4.2.7` instead of the `6.0` I noted above (the CI\\nimage hadn\\u0026#39;t been refreshed). After rebuilding the image to 6.0,\\n`from_file` correctly raises `CouldntDecodeError` on a missing path.\\n\\nSo this is an ffmpeg-version artifact on my side — older ffmpeg\\nemits enough to convince pydub that the input was a 0-length stream,\\nnewer ffmpeg fails hard and pydub correctly surfaces the failure.\\n\\nClosing this from my side — sorry for the noise. (Might be worth a\\nquick line in the README about \\u0026#34;requires ffmpeg \\u0026gt;= 5 for predictable\\nerror behavior\\u0026#34;, but that\\u0026#39;s a docs PR not a code bug.)\",\"state\":\"OPEN\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"BruceKZ\"},\"created_at\":\"2026-05-22T11:11:19Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-05-22T11:11:19Z\"}],\"totalCount\":1,\"pageInfo\":{\"hasNextPage\":false,\"hasPreviousPage\":false,\"startCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQxMToxMToxOVrPAAAAAQxZKzE=\",\"endCursor\":\"Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpK0MjAyNi0wNS0yMlQxMToxMToxOVrPAAAAAQxZKzE=\"}}", "id": "lc_9660941b-b055-4d88-b9d0-be8f0816777e"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "list_issues", "id": "f48701c1-e858-43f9-bf36-b502b5601bfc", "tool_call_id": "call_9ccabdbbca53494387ebf82c", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
